  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Centre for Disaster Protection (the Centre) is the UK&apos;s flagship Disaster Risk Finance (DRF) technical assistance Programme. It supports developing countries to strengthen their pre-disaster planning and financial arrangements so they can respond more rapidly and effectively when a disaster strikes, thereby reducing the impact on people and helping to safeguard economic development. The Centre works with a wide range of partners including country governments, development banks, humanitarian agencies, development insurers, private sector actors, leading research institutions and NGOs.</narrative>
